This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as cognates detection. Additionally, the use of global constraints and reranking methods suggests a focus on improving the accuracy of existing models, which is a common theme in the sub-category. The paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) due to the use of state of the art models and performance improvements. The use of large datasets and different data size conditions may also make the paper relevant to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
